sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant SNS as SNS topic
    participant SQ as sms-q<br/>(filter: channels ∋ sms)
    participant SM as SMS λ
    participant CON as SmsConsent<br/>(DDB · opt-in/out)
    participant BUD as Tenant SMS budget<br/>(atomic counter)
    participant PROV as SMS provider<br/>(SNS/Pinpoint · Twilio pluggable)
    participant USR as Recipient phone
    participant IN as Inbound λ<br/>(STOP / HELP / START)
    participant DLQ as sms-DLQ

    SNS->>SQ: stage=deliver · channels ∋ sms
    SQ->>SM: receive
    Note over SM: resolvable type? delivery-time resolved-check → suppress if resolved
    SM->>CON: check consent (user / externalPhone)
    alt opted_out
        CON-->>SM: opted_out
        Note over SM: suppress + audit suppressed:opted_out — no send (legal)
    else opted_in
        CON-->>SM: ok
        SM->>BUD: atomic check tenant SMS budget/rate
        alt over budget
            BUD-->>SM: denied
            Note over SM: degrade to no-SMS + admin alert (no surprise bill)
        else ok
            BUD-->>SM: ok
            Note over SM: render SHORT template · encoding-aware (GSM-7 160 / UCS-2 70)<br/>segment ≤ maxSegments · country → sender-ID / number pool · minimal content
            SM->>PROV: send (per-country sender id)
            alt accepted
                PROV-->>SM: messageId
                Note over SM: audit: sms_sent
                PROV-->>SM: DLR: delivered | failed{reason}
                Note over SM: audit: sms_delivered | sms_failed
            else transient failure / throttle
                Note over SM,SQ: backoff retry → sms-DLQ after maxReceive
                SQ->>DLQ: ALARM
            end
        end
    end

    Note over USR,CON: opt-out is always honored, out of band
    USR->>IN: texts STOP
    IN->>CON: status=opted_out (suppression list grows)
    Note over IN: START re-subscribes · HELP returns info — audited
